.TH B 1 "January 2026" "git-branch-selector 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
b \- interactive Git branch selector using fuzzy finding
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B b
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B b
is an interactive Git branch selector that uses fzf (fuzzy finder) to help you
quickly switch between Git branches. It displays recently used branches from
git reflog with a preview of commit history.
.PP
The script uses git reflog to show branches you've previously checked out,
allowing you to fuzzy search and select a branch interactively. Each branch
is shown with a preview of its commit history including commit hashes, dates,
messages, and authors.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B git
Required for Git repository operations and reflog access.
.TP
.B fzf
Required for interactive fuzzy finding and branch selection.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run inside any Git repository to select and checkout a branch:
.B b
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success - branch was selected and checked out successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Error - not in a Git repository, fzf not installed, no branches found,
no branch selected, or checkout failed.
.SH AUTHOR
Alexander Schrab
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR git-checkout (1),
.BR git-reflog (1),
.BR fzf (1)
